extensionName.description: Please keep in mind that these strings had to be approved by the Google Brand Features Team. Be sure to make clear that this extension is *FOR* Google Calendar and not *BY* Google. Also, it was explicitly stated, that the phrase 'Google Calendar' should be localized just as it is on the localized versions of the Google Calendar UI.

gdata.migration.title.message: Imrich mìosachain a tha ri leughadh a-mhàin

gdata.migration.description.message: Mhothaich solaraiche mìosachan Ghoogle gu bheil mìosachain agad nach urrainn dhaibh inntrigeadh a dhèanamh do mhìosachan Ghoogle ach ann am modh ri leughadh a-mhàin. Ma tha thu airson gin dhe na mìosachain seo leasachadh, tagh iad gu h-ìosal

gdata.wizard.session.description.message: Tagh seisean làithreach no cuir a-steach seòladh puist-d gus seisean ùr a chruthachadh. Chan fheum thu ach aon seisean do gach cunntas.

gdata.wizard.calendars.description.message: Tagh na mìosachain 's liostaichean nan saothraichean a bu mhath leat fo-sgrìobhadh thuca.

gdata.wizard.nextstep.description.message: Suidhichidh tu na mìosachain agad san ath-cheum.

busyTitle.description: Events with only free/busy access don't have a title, they will use this title instead. The calendar name is used as a parameter, since its often named after the person whose calendar you are viewing.

calendar_name.example: The name of the calendar, e.g. 'Home'
